      "damageFormula": "",
      "healFormula": "",
      "savingThrow": "none",
      "effect": "This spell summons a type 1 spirit wolf, a powerful spirit of nature, that attacks the caster’s enemies. The wolf appears wherever the caster designates within the spell’s range and acts as the caster’s pet (see the “Pets” sidebar in Chapter 8: Using Magic). The pet attacks the caster’s opponents to the best of its ability beginning on the round after it is first summoned, and can be directed not to attack or to attack only particular enemies, toreturn to the caster's side, to guard the caster, or to perform other actions. A caster can have only one summoned petatatime. The spirit wolf is permanent, remaining until dismissed by the caster (or by the caster’s reclaim energy spell) or destroyed. The spirit wolf is considered a summoned creature for the purposes of determining what spells and abilities will affect it. Complete Healing Alteration (Healing)",
