      "attackMode": "",
      "attackBonus": 0,
      "description": "<p>The druid can teleport from any point within a geographical area, such as a forest or chain of mountains, to any other location within the boundaries of that geographical feature. For instance, the spell could teleport the caster from the druid circle in the Dreadlands to the entrance of certain caves within the Dreadlands that lead to the coastal valley of the outpost city Firona Vie. Or she could teleport from the entrance to the city of Erud on the northern edge of the Toxxulia Forest to the entrance to Paineel on the southern edge of the same forest. The druid need not have been to the location she wishes to reach, but she does need to specify a distance she wishes to teleport, and if the distance would take her outside the geographical boundaries, then the spell automatically fails. If the druid has already been to the location to which she wishes to teleport, then no distance need be specified. Elemental: Air Conjuration (Summoning)</p><p><strong>Target/Effect:</strong> Caster</p><p><strong>Spell Resistance:</strong> Yes (object)</p>"
