      "effect": "This spell summons a type 1 air elemental, a spirit of wind, that attacks the caster’s enemies. The elemental appears wherever the caster designates within the spell’s range and acts as the caster’s pet (see the “Pets” sidebar in Chapter 8: Using Magic). The pet attacks the caster’s opponents to the best of its ability beginning on the round after it is first summoned, and can be directed not toattack or to attack only particularenemies, toretum tothe caster’s side, to guard the caster, or to perform other actions. The elemental can be equipped with weapons and shields once it is summoned. However, any equipment it uses disappears along with the elemental when it is destroyed or dismissed. The air elemental can become invisible at will, as per the invisibility spell. It also has a stunning attack, which it can use once per round as an attack action, that duplicates the effect of the stun spell. The elemental regenerates 1 point of damage per round. A caster can have only one summoned pet at a time. The elemental is permanent, remaining until dismissed by the caster (or by the caster’s reclaim energy spell) or destroyed. The elemental is considered both a summoned creature and an elemental for the purposes of determining what spells and abilities will affect it. Elementalkin: Earth Conjuration (Summoning)",
