      "deliveryType": "utility",
      "attackMode": "",
      "attackBonus": 0,
      "description": "<p>The caster summons the mortal remains of any one being within range to his side, so long as the corpse is that of a creature that has died within a number of days past equal to the caster’s level. The spell imparts no life to the corpse; it merely summons it to the caster’s side. The corpse appears within the coffin supplied as the spell’s material component. The caster need not know the target&#x27;s location within the spell’s range. This spell will not affect an undead creature, but only the corpse of a truly dead creature. 750 gp value, of a size to hold the summoned corpse.</p><p><strong>Material Component:</strong> A coffin of at least</p><p><strong>Target/Effect:</strong> See text</p><p><strong>Spell Resistance:</strong> No</p>"
