      "effect": "This spell magically forces the target to remain in its current location. The target may continue to act normally, fighting or casting spells, for example, but it cannot take any move actions. The target may use a teleport spell, but once the teleportation has relocated him, the target will still be rooted in his new location. The root effect lasts for 1d8 rounds (this roll is made in secret by the GM), but each time the target ishitbyaspell that causes instantaneous damage, such as shock of fire, it is allowed another Reflex save. Additional saves are not granted if the spells cause continual damage over more than 1 round, such as winged death or any “rain” spell.",
