      "duration": "1d4 rounds",
      "damageFormula": "",
      "healFormula": "",
      "savingThrow": "none",
      "effect": "This spell can reduce the duration of any one school of magic in effect on the target at the time of casting, as long as the spell or spell-like effect does not have the [poison] or [disease] descriptors. At the time of casting, the caster selects one school of magic (e.g., alteration, abjuration, etc.), and any spells of that school currently active on the target are affected. Such spells and their effects will be annulled at the same time that taper enchantment ends. To determine whether this tapering takes place, the enchanter makes a dispel check for each spell of the selected school by rolling 1d20 + 1 per caster level (maximum +10), versus a DC of 11 + the caster level of the one who cast the spell being tapered. Taper enchantment has no effect on spells of instantaneous duration, nor does it heal any damage caused by the tapered spell prior to the time the spell is cancelled.",
