      "damageFormula": "",
      "healFormula": "",
      "savingThrow": "none",
      "effect": "The caster is turned into a tree of whatever type is most common in the area in which the spell is cast and becomes literally rooted to the spot where the spell is cast. While in this form, the caster recovers an additional 2 hit points every 5 minutes. He retains his normal AC but does not gain the benefit of any Dexterity modifiers. The caster is also indistinguishable from normal trees, except by those who can detect magical effects or recognize shapeshifted beings. The caster cannot see while in tree form, but he remains aware of his surroundings and can hear conversations that take place nearby or sense the approach of others. Additionally, he may cast spells as normal. Finally, the caster is slightly more susceptible to fire attacks, and he gains a—1 buff penalty to fire saves, and fire resistance (— 4). [A resistance penalty can never reduce a target’s resistance to less than (0).]",
