      "savingThrow": "none",
      "effect": "This spell creates an animated +5 warhammer. The unswerving hammer of faith is treated in all ways as a pet (see the “Pets” sidebar in Chapter 8: Using Magic).Upon completion of casting, the cleric designates one target within range that the hammer will attack; the hammer appears beside that opponent and attacks once per round, beginning on the round in which it appears. The animated warhammer cannot be otherwise commanded. The hammer's attack bonus is equal to the caster’s base attack bonus (not including its +5 enhancement bonus). It can move at the caster’s base speed, and will pursue its target unceasingly until either the target or the caster is killed; once summoned, it can move freely beyond the spell’s range. If the hammer is unable to locate its target for 10 rounds (for example, if the target becomes invisible or teleports away), it disappears. Note, however, that the hammer can be enhanced with spells such as see invisible or buff-type spells, as any other pet.",
