        "rawText": "Chokidai\n\n=\n\n\"RPG: MONnSTErsc ) NO rTrTratyn._---- _ 17 ¥] 4 Je\nLis dep Reb x = poe HISLEN SO} 2 tls das <:> la Ad> Pen, Se! a 4 Hf - ae \"*\n\nChokidai are large reptilian beasts\ncreated by the sarnaks of Chardok\nto serve as guardians and hunt-\n\ners. Bred from the scaled\n\nwolves native to Kunark,\nthe chokidai are ru-\n\nHit Dice: 26d10+130 (273 hp)\n\nInitiative: +4 (Dex)\n\nSpeed: 40 ft.\n\nAC: 43 (-Isize, +4 Dex, +3 studded leather, +27 natural)\n\nAttacks: 2 claws +35 melee, bite +33 melee\n\nDamage: Claw 2d6+7; bite 3d6+4 and mangle\n\nFace/Reach 5 ft. by 10 Ft./5 ft.\n\nSpecial Attacks: Drag down, mangle\n\nSpecial Qualities Damage reduction 25/+3, fast healing 6, scent,\nultravision\n\nSaves: Fort +20, Ref +17, Will +7\n\nAbilities: Str 27, Dex 18, Con 21, Int 4, Wis 13, Cha 8\n\nSkills: Listen +25, Spot +25, Wilderness Lore +7*\n\nFeats: Alertness, Cleave (claws only), Multiattack, Power\nAttack\n\nClimate/Terrain Underground\n\nOrganization Solitary, pair, or pack (3-7)\n\nChallenge Rating 20\n\nTreasure: None\n\nAlignment: Usually neutral\n\nAdvancement Range: 27-35HD (Large); 36-50HD\n(Huge); 51-70 HD\n(Gargantuan)\n\nFaction: Sarnak Collective\n\nDescription\n\n_\n\né md :\nmored to be the result « hag? a\n\nof the sarnaks' own experiments of mixing the\n\nblood of Skyfire wurms with\n\n- - _*\n\nsms . Tse\n\nChokidai are reptilian creatures almost as large as a horse. They\nhave reddish scales fading to a pinkish-white toward their bellies\nand legs. Several sharp, fin-like scales protrude from the back of\nthe chokidai, each 12 to 18 inches high and of a grayish-green\n\ncolor. Their muzzles sport large razor-sharp teeth, and they have\nblack, vicious claws.\n\nChokidai are now raised and trained by the Brood of DiZok\nsarnak in their fastness of Chardok. The sarnak royals have larger\nchokidai as bodyguards and pets for their children, while the outer\nguards use them as scouts, guards, and hunters. The chokidai's\n\nkeen senses alert sarnak sentries of intruders they might otherwise\nmiss.\n\nThe chokidai are completely loyal to their sarnak masters, who\ntreat them as honored pets and feed them well with the raw meat\n\nof slain enemies. Iksar and elven meat is said to be very tasty to\nthem.\n\nSarnaks often equip their pet chokidai with reinforced leather\nshoulder-plates (spaulders). The sarnak will decorate these leathers with the colors of their house and lineage, indicating to whom\nthe chokidai belongs. Chokidai who perform well also have\nmarkings made upon these spaulders indicating what deeds the\n\n;\n\nee\n\nor a\"\nys\n\nparticular chokidai has performed. ;\n\nA chokidai might rarely have treasure, but only if it has ‘\nswallowed something that lodged in its gullet. The intact spinal\ntidges of a chokidai can be used to make durable and sharp dagger- 4\nlike weapons. :\n\n.\nCombat ;\n\nThe chokidai spends much of its time in guard duty, either at c\n\na single location or as part of a patrol. Though they are not highly ?\nintelligent, chokidai are smart enough to accept reasonably com- '\n\nplex commands and can patrol areas and report intruders - or xe\nattempt to kill intruders quickly if it thinks it can. If a chokidai is\nwith a master, it will always follow its master's orders. If in a group '\n\nand no masters are around (or none are giving orders), chokidai f\n\nwill all tend to attack one opponent until it is down and then ;\n\nmove onto the next. rf\n.\n\nf\n\nDrag Down (Ex): A chokidai that hits with a bite attack can\nattempt to drag down its opponentasa free action. This works like\n\na trip attack (see EverQuest: Player's Handbook, page 378), but\n\ndoes not require a touch attack nor provoke attacks of opportu- b>\nnity. If the attempt fails, the opponent cannot react to trip the\n\nchokidai.\n\n4\nMangle (Ex): Ifa chokidai hits a target with its tearing bite, the if\ntarget must make a Reflex save (DC 28) or take an additional ?\n\n3d6+13 points of slashing damage and continue to x\n\nbleed for 3 hp per round. A Heal check (DC 15) 4\nwill staunch this bleeding.\n\nSkills: Chokidai have incredibly acute :\nsenses, conferring a +12 racial bonus 2\nto Listen and _ Spot. .\n*Chokidai have a +8 bo- ‘\nnus to Wilderness Lore ‘\nwhen tracking by\nscent. P\n\nAuwen\n\nother strange creatures native to\nKunark. Out of countless failed experiments, the chokidai have emerged as\nperhaps the lone success - but what a\nfearsome creation they are."
