        "rawText": "Ebon Drake\n\nLarge Dragon\n\n6d12+12 (51 hp)\n\nInitiative: +5 (+1 Dex, +4 Improved Initiative)\nSpeed: 30 ft., fly 120 ft. (average)\n\nAC: 18 (-1 size, +1 Dex, +8 natural)\nAttacks:\n\nDamage:\nFace/Reach:\nSpecial Attacks:\n\nHit Dice:\n\n2 claws +6 melee, bite +1 melee\n\nClaw Id6+1; bite 2d6\n5 ft. by 10 Ft./5 ft.\n\nBreath weapon\n\nSpecial Qualities: Ebon field, immunities, fire resistance (8), ultravision\n\nSaves: Fort +7, Ref +6, Will +7\n\nAbilities: Str 12, Dex 13, Con 15, Int 13, Wis 14, Cha 12\n\nSkills: Hide +6*, Jump +7, Knowledge (any one) +4, Listen +11,\nSneak +7, Spot +11\n\nFeats: Flyby Attack, Improved Initiative\n\nTemperate hill or mountains\n: Solitary\n\nChallenge Rating: 4\nStandard\n\nUsually neutral\n\nAdvancement Range: 7-12 HD (Large); 13-18 HD (Huge)\nFaction: None\n\nKa\n\nNecromancer Abilities: Asa 30th-level necromancer, Zlandicar\nhas greater specialization (evocation), as well as the fear storm,\ninvisibility to undead, and rebuke undead (x2) death masteries. See\n\nthe description of the necromancer in Chapter 3: Classes of the\nEverQuest: Player's Handbook for details of these abilities.\n\nFire Drake\n\nLarge Dragon (Fire)\n\n8d12+32 (84 hp)\n\n+7 (+5 Dex, +4 Improved Initiative)\n30 ft., fly 120 ft. (average)\n\n20 (-I size, +5 Dex, +6 natural)\n\n2 claws +10 melee, bite +5 melee\nClaw 1d6+3; bite 2d6+1 and 1Id6 fire\n5 ft. by 10 Ft./5 ft.\n\nBreath weapon, fiery maw\n\nDamage shield (3), immunities, fire subtype, ultravision\nFort +10, Ref +11, Will +7\n\nStr 16, Dex 20, Con 18, Int 14, Wis 16, Cha 10\n\nAppraise +10, Bluff +8, Jump +11, Knowledge (any two) +10, Listen\n+11, Safe Fall +13, Spot +11\n\nFlyby Attack, Improved Initiative, Power Attack\nWarm mountains\n\nSolitary\n6\n\nStandard\nUsually neutral\n7-14 HD (Large);15-20 HD (Huge)\n\nNone\n\n-- ?\n> oe, 4A 2 = 7\n= Fa Ee ee oe Oe SS Ee\n\n10d12+20 (85 hp)\n\n+6 (+2 Dex, +4 Improved Initiative)\n30 ft., Fly 120 ft. (average)\n\n17 (-1 size, +2 Dex, +8 natural)\n\n2 claws +12 melee; bite +7 melee\n\nClaw 1d8+3; bite 2d6+1\n\n5 ft. by 10 Ft./5 Ft.\nBreath weapon\nImmunities, fire resistance (12), ultravision\n\nFort +7, Ref +7, Will +10\nStr 16, Dex 14, Con 14, Int 14, Wis 16, Cha 14\n\nHide +8%*, Intimidate +12, Jump +13, Knowledge (any two) +12,\n\nListen +13, Sneak +12, Spot +13\nFlyby Attack, Improved Initiative, Power Attack\nTemperate mountains\nSolitary\n6\nStandard\nUsually neutral\n: 11-20 HD (Large); 21-25 HD (Huge)\n\nNone\n\nDescription\n\nWhile the dragons are the greatest of their kind, a number of\nlesser creatures call themselves kin to the great dragons. The\ndrakes are one such creature. While drakes come in a variety of\n\ncolors, they do have the same basic form: they are hexapedal\ncreatures, with a set of claws, aset of legs, and a set of sizable wings.\n\nFine scales cover most of a drake's body, while larger, tougher\nscales cover the underbelly.\n\nDrakes tend to be loners except when mating or raising young.\nThey hunt most anything, making no distinction between a bear,\na bird, or a human for where their find their next meal. Most of its\nlife, a drake contents itself simply with enjoying the day, sunning\nitself on a rock, taking a quick lava bath if it likes that sort of\nactivity, or perusing interesting trophies it has gathered in its lair.\n\nCombat\n\nDrakes feel confident attacking almost any creature, especially if it does not fly. The drake will\npass over with its breath weapon until its prey is\nready to be eaten instead of ready to fight back.\nShould an opponent prove capable of injuring\nthe drake while it is airborne, it will likely fly away to find easier\nprey; or, if it is hungry enough, it will land on its prey and begin\ntearing with its teeth and claws.\n\nImmunities (Ex): All drakes are immune to sleep and paralysis effects, but they do not share the other immunities their larger\ndragon kin.\n\nEbon Orake\n\nDescription\n\nEbon drakes are\nuniformly glossy black\nin color, covered in a\nshifting aura of darkness. They do not enjoy\nhigh altitudes like some of their fellow drakes,\ninstead preferring hills and low-lying moun-\n\n15d12+75 (172 hp)\n\n+8 (+4 Dex, +4 Improved Initiative)\n30 ft., fly 120 ft. (average)\n\n26 (- size, +4 Dex +13 natural)\n\n2 claws +20 melee; bite +18 melee\nClaw 1d8+6; bite 2d6+3\n\n5 ft. by 10 Ft./5 ft.\n\nBreath weapon\n\nDamage reduction 15/+2, immunities, fire resistance (20),\nultravision\n\nFort +14, Ref +13, Will +13\nStr 23, Dex 18, Con 20, Int 16, Wis 18, Cha 16\n\nHide +18*, Intimidate +21, Jump +21, Knowledge (any two) +18,\nLanguage (any one) +6, Listen +21, Sneak +17, Spot +21\n\nFlyby Attack, Improved Initiative, Multiattack, Power Attack\nTemperate mountains\n\nSolitary\n\n12\n\nStandard\n\nUsually neutral\n\n16-25 HD (Large); 26-35 HD (Huge)\n\nNone\n\nCombat\n\nWeakest of the dragon-kin, an ebon drake will usually try to\nescape a fight that goes against it, breaking away when it is reduced\nto half its hit points or less.\n\nBreath Weapon (Su): The ebon drake can breathe a 20-foot\ncone of fire as an attack action once every 1d4 rounds. This deals\n\n1d8 points of fire damage to all in the area, although a Reflex save\n(DC 15) will halve this damage.\n\nEbon Field (Su): The ebon drake is covered in a shifting layer\nof supernatural darkness that gives it perpetual one-half concealment (20% miss chance), even against attackers with low-light\nvision or ultravision.\n\nSkills: *An ebon drake's ebon field and dark coloration confer\nupon it a +8 bonus to Hide checks in dark or shadowy conditions."
