        "rawText": "eruptions of lava. As with the lava beetle, some scholars postulate\n‘ok that the dragon Nagafen altered a simple giant spider to create the\nOescri ption lava duct crawlers. Certainly, lava duct crawlers appear in considerThe dragon Nagafen isrumored to have taken the common fire beetle able numbers around the Lavastorm Mountains, where Nagafen is\nand magically altered it to create the powerful lava beetles that now said to reside.\nprotect the outer portions of his lair and have since roamed throughout The lava duct crawler is a hunting carnivore that lives off the\nthe Lavastorm Mountains and beyond. Other accounts report finding flesh of other beings in the\nthese magical beetles in other volcanic areas of Norrath, however, thus volcanic\n\nCombat\n\ndamage each round to all in that area. Further, they effectively\ngain the benefit of a [heat] damage shield (5) at all times. Any\nweapon that strikes the lava beetle takes 5 points of fire damage\nwith each successful hit, as well.\n\nLarge Magical Beast (Fire)\n\nperhaps discrediting the Nagafen theory.\nLava beetles are typically 9 to 10 feet long and appear much\n\nlike their smaller kin, the common fire beetle, with a yellow\nand orange carapace and black legs.\n\nThe lava beetle is an aggressive beast and will\nattack those creatures that enter into its territory\nwith its mandibles.\n\nFiery Bite (Ex): The lava beetle may make\na Proc check (DC 14) with each successful bite\nattack; ifa check is successful, the target of the\n\nbite takes an additional (6d6) x 2 points of fire\ndamage from the beetle's fiery mucus. This\nadditional damage is not multiplied with a\nsuccessful critical hit.\n\nFire Subtype: Fire immunity; double damage from cold except on a successful save.\n\nHeat Aura (Ex): Lava beetles radiate scorching heat in a 10-foot radius, dealing 1d4 points of fire"
